<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8083&amp;p=94418#p94418"><![CDATA[
A simple solution would be to do like the 3-in-1s for DS Slot 1 do and flash a boot-able rom to non-volatile memory (like NAND or flash rom) and have it so if the device doesn't see an SD card in the device, it boots from said flash/nand/what have you and acts like a regular GB/GBC game.<br /><br />This would allow you to use it with stuff like the SGB and N64 pokemon transfer pack.<br /><br />Might be hard to fit that all in a small form factor though...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5283">DNSDies</a> — Thu May 24, 2012 10:54 am</p><hr />
